The paper presents a framework for learning with probability distributions using distance-based discriminative methods. This is a common problem in machine learning and can be applied to various subfields such as computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the theoretical foundations of the approach, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper focuses on a specific learning framework.
